{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> τροπ-ή</b>, ἡ, <br /> (τρέπω) <b>turn, turning</b>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> τροπαὶ ἠελίοιο: <br /><Level4><b>__I.a</b></Level4> ὅθι τροπαὶ ἠελίοιο apparently denotes a point on the horizon, probably the West or place where the sum sets (so [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis 1787.20), 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.404. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__I.b</b></Level4> each of two fixed points in the solar year, <b>the solstices,</b> first in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus, ἠελίοιο τροπῇς \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<b>at the time of the (winter) solstice, </b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Op.” 479; μετὰ τροπὰς ἠελ. [prev. work]564,663 (with _Doric dialect_ _accusative_ _plural_ in -ᾰς); πεδὰ τὰς τροπάς 7th c.BC: Alcman Lyricus 33.5:—later the two solstices were distinguished as τροπαὶ θεριναί and χειμεριναί, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.19, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.16, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 767c, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 542b4ff, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 6.405, etc. (rarely in _sing._, τροπὴ θερινή 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 364b2, 1st c.BC: Geminus Astronomicus 1.13 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; τ. χειμερινή[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 15); τροπαὶ νότιοι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 542b11 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τ. βόρειοι, νότιοι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.601a:\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] —when τροπαί is used alone, it mostly refers to <b>the winter solstice,</b> but the sense is always determined by the context, see [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] [same places]; περὶ ἡλίου τροπάς (i.e. χειμερινάς) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.39; εὐθὺς ἐκ τροπῶν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 542b20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—sometimes also of other heavenly bodies, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 39d; περὶ Πλειάδος δύσιν καὶ τροπάς 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 542b23, etc.; ἄστρων ἐπιτολάς, δύσεις, τροπάς 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 30.5; τροπὰς τῶν ἐνδεδεμένων ἄστρων 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Caelo” 296b4; τροπαὶ ἡλίου καὶ σελήνης 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 2p.40U.:—sometimes four in number (the two equinoxes and two solstices), 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 5.11, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 17(1).22; so (on a sun-dial) θερινὴ τ., ἰσημερινὴ τ., χειμερινὴ τ., Ἀρχ.Δελτ. 12.236 (from Samos). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>turn, change,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1316a17; πλείους τραπόμενος τροπὰς τοῦ Εὐρίπου 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.90 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τ. πρὸς τὸ βέλτιον <b>turn</b> for the better, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 2.25S.; ὀξυτέρας τρεπόμενος τ. τοῦ χαμαιλέοντος 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Alcibiades” 23; αἱ τοῦ κόλακος ὥσπερ πολύποδος τ. [prev. author] 2.52f; αἱ τῶ αἵματος τ. καὶ ἀλλοιώσιες 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 102c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἱ περὶ τὸν ἀέρα τ. <b>changes</b> in the air or weather, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.946f\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of wine, <b>a turning sour,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]939f (compare τροπίας)\">Refs</a>]; <b>going bad,</b> of food, τ. καὶ διαφθορὰ τῶν παρακειμένων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 19.208 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of phonetic <b>change</b> in language, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Adverbiis;” 210.4, Hdn.Gr. 2.932. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> τροπαὶ λέξεως <b>a change</b> of speech <b>by figures</b> or <b>tropes</b> (τρόποι), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Dem.Enc.” 6, compare 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ εὑρέσεως” 4.10, +others \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.4</b></Level3> αἱ τροπαί, ={αἱ τροπαῖαι}, <b>alternating</b> winds, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 940b16, 21, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 2.3.1, “Vent.” 26. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>the turning about of the enemy, putting to flight</b> or <b>routing</b> him, τροπήν (or τροπάς) τινος ποιεῖν or ποιεῖσθαι put one to <b>flight,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.30, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 246 (troch.), 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.19, 6.69, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἵαν ἂν τροπὴν Εὐρυσθέως θείμην (θείην codices) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 743; τροπὴ γινομένη 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.167, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.49, 50, etc.: poetry, ἐν μάχης τροπῇ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1237 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν τροπῇ δορός in <b>the rout</b> caused by the spear, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1275, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 82. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> used by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus for θέσις,\">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>] <b>position,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 985b17, 1042b14, compare 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 4.5.2, 4.5.6. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>a coin,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]; compare τροπαϊκόν.","strongNumber":"G5157","accentedUnicode":"τροπή","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5158","matchingForm":"τρόπος","stepTransliteration":"tropos","gloss":"way","_zh_tw_Gloss":"樣, 像, 方法","_es_Gloss":"manera","_zh_Gloss":"样, 像, 方法"}],"shortDef":"shifting, turning, variation, change","mediumDef":"shifting, turning, variation, change <br /><b>a turning round; a turning back, change, mutation, variation, shifting, change</b> <ref='Jas.1.17'>Jas. 1:17</ref>*","stepGloss":"turning","stepTransliteration":"tropē","count":1,"_es_Definition":"girar, cambiar, variación","_zh_tw_Definition":"轉動, 改變 (雅1:17)","_zh_Definition":"转动, 改变 (雅1:17)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự thay đổi; sự xoay vòng, vòng quay, cuộc cách mạng. (Hapax). động từ τρέπω: quay, xoay, đổi hướng; đảo lộn.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"轉動","_es_Gloss":"variación","_zh_Gloss":"转动"}]}